President Joe Biden delivers a speech at the South Lawn, thanking those involved in the passage of the bipartisan infrastructure bill. He emphasizes the importance of the bill in addressing the needs and concerns of the American people, such as finding work, supporting small businesses, and improving education. The president expresses his commitment to building back better and creating a stronger, more resilient nation. He highlights key provisions of the law, including the replacement of lead pipes, expansion of high-speed internet access, investment in roads and bridges, and the promotion of clean energy and electric vehicles. Biden also emphasizes the importance of compromise and consensus in getting things done and announces the appointment of Mitch Landrieu to oversee the implementation of the law. He concludes by stating that this is a historic moment that will shape the future of the country.